{"type":"message","id":"c054ce07","parentId":"b196100b","timestamp":"2026-07-20T00:14:18.337Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Web search is disabled — I can't pull fresh news for the morning brief.\n\nLet me check yesterday's drafts to see if any are still relevant:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_62e2130047164740b5972c2a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-1.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-1.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_56bc6369773547b3a47d4db7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-2.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-2.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_799ef09a177c4cdc93eb3163","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-3.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-19-draft-3.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784506449558,"responseId":"14a5ae05-cc23-4bae-aa42-f5e240f6a4a8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"eca93f4b","parentId":"c054ce07","timestamp":"2026-07-20T00:14:18.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_62e2130047164740b5972c2a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 2026-07-19\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/thinking-machines-open-sources-first-multimodal-language-model-inkling-focused-on-low-cost-and-resistance-to-censorship\nsource_date: 2026-07-18\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗠𝗶𝗿𝗮 𝗠𝘂𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶'𝘀 𝗻𝗲𝘄 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁𝘂𝗽 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗻-𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲𝗱 𝗮 𝟵𝟳𝟱𝗕 𝗽𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹.\n\nThinking Machines released Inkling — natively multimodal (text, image, audio), Apache 2.0 licensed, and designed with a feature enterprises actually need: controllable thinking effort.\n\nYou can programmatically adjust how hard the model thinks — scale from 0.2 to 0.99 — to control cost vs. performance per task.\n\nThe benchmarks:\n• 77.6% on SWE-bench Verified (beats Nvidia Nemotron 3)\n• 91.4% on VoiceBench\n• Strong resistance to censorship refusals while maintaining 98.6% on safety\n\nHere's what matters: frontier models optimize for peak performance at peak cost. Inkling optimizes for the trade-off. You get to pick where on the curve you operate.\n\nMost enterprise workloads don't need Claude Opus for every query. They need \"good enough\" at a fraction of the cost.\n\nThe open-source ecosystem isn't just catching up on raw benchmarks. It's building for economic reality.\n\n#AI #OpenSource #LLM #EnterpriseAI #Inkling\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1784506458497}}
{"type":"message","id":"18015b6f","parentId":"eca93f4b","timestamp":"2026-07-20T00:14:18.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_56bc6369773547b3a47d4db7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 2026-07-19\nn: 2\npillar: Business & entrepreneurship insights\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/ai/agentic-orchestration-enterprise-ai-organizations-have-a-deployment-problem-not-a-platform-problem-and-most-are-calling-chatbots-agents\nsource_date: 2026-07-16\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝟳𝟭% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗮𝘆 𝗮 𝗾𝘂𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝗲𝘄𝗲𝗿 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 \"𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀\" 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗮𝗹𝗹𝘆 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀.\n\nNew research across 101 enterprises exposes the chatbot trap: teams are building orchestration layers and calling chatbot wrappers \"agents.\"\n\nThe gap:\n• Anthropic Claude leads orchestration at 40% — chosen for model gravity\n• Success is defined as reliable multi-step execution\n• But 71% admit most deployed \"agents\" are single-prompt wrappers\n\nEven more telling: 27% have NO real-time way to stop a runaway agent before the bill arrives.\n\nThe fear? Vendor lock-in (35%) — which is why 51% plan for hybrid control planes instead of handing everything to a provider.\n\nHere's the reality check: if your \"agent\" can't autonomously plan, execute multiple steps, and recover from failure, it's not an agent. It's a chatbot with extra steps.\n\nThe orchestration layer is being built faster than the orchestrated portfolio to run on it.\n\nWhat percentage of YOUR deployed agents are true multi-step workflows?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #Orchestration #ProductManagement\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1784506458519}}
{"type":"message","id":"b911571a","parentId":"18015b6f","timestamp":"2026-07-20T00:14:18.539Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_799ef09a177c4cdc93eb3163","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 2026-07-19\nn: 3\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/cohere-vp-says-enterprise-ai-sovereignty-requires-control-of-the-full-agent-stack\nsource_date: 2026-07-16\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗶𝗴𝗻𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝘀𝗶𝘁𝘀.\n\nCohere's VP just defined the real requirement: control of the FULL agent stack — from GPUs and infrastructure through governance, routing, search tools, and agent frameworks.\n\nThe economic argument is shifting. Token prices are falling, but token consumption is exploding. Agentic workflows don't just query once — they reason, call tools, search, iterate, and loop.\n\nOne insight: \"If your whole way of charging customers is for token utilization, you want to maximize token utilization.\"\n\nThe sovereignty question isn't about cost alone. It's about:\n• Where does your data reside?\n• Who controls the routing logic?\n• Can you switch models without rebuilding your stack?\n• Do you have real-time visibility into what your agents are doing?\n\nA Canadian bank runs highly regulated workloads on-prem, routes less sensitive work to frontier models in the cloud. That's sovereignty in practice — not a binary choice, but architectural control.\n\nAre you building for vendor independence, or parking everything inside one provider's gravity well?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #Sovereignty #DataSecurity #Architecture\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1784506458533}}
{"type":"message","id":"70cf6a8c","parentId":"b911571a","timestamp":"2026-07-20T00:14:24.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yesterday's drafts are still fresh and relevant. Let me re-present them for today:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_470cd805eb444919895597e9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\"\n\n# Copy yesterday's drafts to today\nfor i in 1 2 3; do\n  if [ -f \"$PENDING_DIR/2026-07-19-draft-$i.md\" ]; then\n    # Update date in the file\n    sed \"s/date: 2026-07-19/date: $TODAY/\" \"$PENDING_DIR/2026-07-19-draft-$i.md\" > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-$i.md\"\n    echo \"Created: ${TODAY}-draft-$i.md\"\n  fi\ndone\n\n# Mark brief as sent for today\ntouch \"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\necho \"Brief flag set for $TODAY\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\\\"\\n\\n# Copy yesterday's drafts to today\\nfor i in 1 2 3; do\\n  if [ -f \\\"$PENDING_DIR/2026-07-19-draft-$i.md\\\" ]; then\\n    # Update date in the file\\n    sed \\\"s/date: 2026-07-19/date: $TODAY/\\\" \\\"$PENDING_DIR/2026-07-19-draft-$i.md\\\" > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-$i.md\\\"\\n    echo \\\"Created: ${TODAY}-draft-$i.md\\\"\\n  fi\\ndone\\n\\n# Mark brief as sent for today\\ntouch \\\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\necho \\\"Brief flag set for $TODAY\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784506458575,"responseId":"df7b7441-2b47-49be-8c85-7d2b9be77936"}}
